definition: to come to/to awaken/to regain consciousness
to wake up/to be awake/to become aware/to sober up/to come to

sentences.english: The general anesthesia therapy dose are few, regains consciousness thoroughly, rapid, the controllability is good.
sentences.chinese: 全麻藥用量少，甦醒徹底，迅速，可控性好。

sentences.english: Mayo's unrequited love was again ardently and painfully resuscitated .
sentences.chinese: 真夜那沒有結果的愛又甦醒了，再次痛苦地繼續下去。

sentences.english: He who looks outside dreams, he who looks inside awakens.
sentences.chinese: 向外瞅的人在夢中，向內看的人甦醒滅。

sentences.english: Synopsis: An amnesiac spy awakens in a world overrun by zombies.
sentences.chinese: 一個記憶缺失的特工在一個殭屍遍野的世界甦醒。

sentences.english: To simply wake-up and experience this Shiva tattva is Shivratri.
sentences.chinese: 希瓦之夜就是單單的甦醒過來並體驗希瓦。

sentences.english: Peter has fainted;this bucket of water should fetch him round.
sentences.chinese: 彼得昏過去了，這桶水會使他甦醒過來。

sentences.english: As is usually the case, after beer starts to flow, memory rewinds .
sentences.chinese: 如往常一樣，幾杯啤酒下肚後，記憶又甦醒了。

sentences.english: None of them had respiration inhibiting and postponed wakening.
sentences.chinese: 所有病人未發生呼吸抑制及甦醒延遲。

sentences.english: He revives my soul and guides me along right pathways for his name's sake.
sentences.chinese: 祂使我靈魂甦醒，爲自已的名引導我走義路。

sentences.english: The fresh air soon revived him.
sentences.chinese: 新鮮空氣很快使他甦醒。

sentences.english: We saw, a youth has not regained consciousness remnant dream.
sentences.chinese: 我們看到了，一點青春未甦醒的殘夢。

sentences.english: He restores my soul; He guides me on the paths of righteousness ForHis name's sake.
sentences.chinese: 祂使我的魂甦醒，爲自己的名引導我走義路。

sentences.english: He restores my soul. He guides me in paths of righteousness for his name's sake.
sentences.chinese: 祂使我的靈魂甦醒，爲自己的名引導我走義路。
冰水使克莉絲甦醒過來。

sentences.english: Morning is when I am awake and there is a dawn in me.
sentences.chinese: 清晨，在我甦醒之時，曙光已然照臨內心。

sentences.english: The man was stunned, but he came round after a time.
sentences.chinese: 那個人給打昏了，但過了一會兒甦醒了過來。

definition: first tone in Mandarin/high, level tone
to call out (a name etc)/to shout
to talk in one's sleep/crazy talk
to rouse/to be woken by sth/to wake with a start/to sleep lightly
not a sound to be heard (idiom)
talking in one's sleep/delirious ravings/nonsense/sheer fantasy
feudal term of praise for ruler, king or emperor/general term for saint in former times/term for God during the Taiping Heavenly Kingdom 太平天國|太平天国/Holy Spirit (in Christian Trinity)
